			<description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Qwiki is seeking New Media Interns to optimize the Qwiki Creator</strong></p><p><strong>About Qwiki:</strong></p><p>Qwiki is a New York City-based technology company pioneering an easy-to-create&nbsp;new media format that combines the visual appeal of a video with the interactivity&nbsp;of the web. The company recently launched a content creation partnership with&nbsp;ABC News and a distribution partnership with Bing, as covered by several major<br />media outlets.</p><p>Qwiki was founded by serial entrepreneur, Doug Imbruce, and won TechCrunch&nbsp;Disrupt in September 2010. The Company launched its website (www.qwiki.com) in&nbsp;January 2011 and its iPad App in April 2011, which was named by Apple as the top&nbsp;Reference App of 2011 and has over 1 million downloads. Qwiki has raised&nbsp;approximately $10.5 million in funding from a number of high profile investors,&nbsp;including the founders of Facebook, Groupon and YouTube.</p><p><strong>About the Position:</strong></p><p>Qwiki recently launched the Qwiki Creator in partnership with ABC News. The Qwiki&nbsp;Creator allows anyone to quickly and easily create interactive, rich-media content&nbsp;for the first time. As New Media Intern, your primary responsibility will be to assist&nbsp;with the Qwiki Creator quality assurance process.</p><p>In addition, you will:<br />&bull; Create and edit Qwikis for major media companies, celebrities, personalities,<br />professional bloggers, and publishers<br />&bull; Research relevant bloggers and social media influencers<br />&bull; Assist with administrative duties</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>&bull; Pursuing, or recently completed, a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a related field<br />&bull; Strong academic performance<br />&bull; Experience with digital editing and/or producing<br />&bull; Proficient in Final Cut Pro, iMovie, and/or QuickTime<br />&bull; Acute eye for aesthetics<br />&bull; Believes in Qwiki&rsquo;s vision of creating a new media format<br />&bull; Film school experience preferred<br />&bull; Minimum of 15 hours per week requested</p><p><strong>Perks:</strong></p><p>&bull; Transportation and lunch stipend<br />&bull; No barriers to highest levels of management<br />&bull; Talented, passionate, and driven team<br />&bull; Amazing office in the heart of SoHo</p><p><strong>To Apply:</strong></p><p>Submit your application on this page. Please include a resume and a link to your work or portfolio.</p><p><strong>Relevant Press and Links:</strong></p><p><strong>Qwiki - ABC News Partnership Launch:</strong><br />Front Cover of New York Times Business Day: <a href="http://tiny.cc/avbtfw">http://tiny.cc/avbtfw</a><br />Sample Embed from ABC - Death of Junior Seau: <a href="http://tiny.cc/uwbtfw">http://tiny.cc/uwbtfw</a><br />ABC News Channel on Qwiki: <a href="http://www.qwiki.com/ABCnews">http://www.qwiki.com/ABCnews</a></p><p><strong>Example of a blogger using the Qwiki Creator:</strong><br />Shea Marie&rsquo;s Qwiki Channel:<br /><a href="http://www.qwiki.com/CheyenneMeetsChanel">http://www.qwiki.com/CheyenneMeetsChanel</a></p><p><strong>Qwiki - Bing Integration:</strong><br /><a href="http://venturebeat.com/2012/06/12/bing-qwiki/">http://venturebeat.com/2012/06/12/bing-qwiki/</a></p>]]></description>
